OL,6,F"The evidence from all the research is
OL,7,Fthat the benefits of the vaccines, the
OL,8,Fgreatly reduced risk of serious
OL,9,Fillness or death from Covid, far
OL,10,Foutweigh the very small risk of
OL,11,Fserious side-effects such as
OL,12,Fmyocarditis or pericarditis.
OL,14,FDoctor Patterson has written to the
OL,15,FGeneral Medical Council to look at the
OL,16,Fside effects of the vaccine and in
OL,17,Fresponse, they say their role is to
OL,18,Fregulate individual doctors only, so
OL,19,Fthey are legally unable to give advice
OL,20,For comment on clinical matters.
